Suspicions of a technical fault as the cause of the crash grew as callers reported air conditioning issues on similar Helios jets.
Angry relatives demanded answers at Larnaca airport, accusing the airline of negligence.
Aviation experts suggested a loss of cabin pressure led to oxygen deprivation for the pilots.
Witnesses described the chaotic scene as the plane crashed near Grammatiko.
The tragic incident claimed the lives of all 121 people on board.
Rescue workers recovered the black boxes for investigation.
European Union Transport Commissioner expressed condolences and emphasized the need for improved safety measures in air travel.
